               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411213-name-329" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411213-name-329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411213-name-329" type="surname" value="MANEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411213-name-329" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD MANEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am one of the Thames Police-constables. Yes<lb></lb>terday morning, at eleven o'clock, I was at the Fox-under-the-hill cause-way, and saw the prisoner, who is what we call a "shore-raker"—he was near the barge <hi rend="italic">Charlotte</hi>, belonging to Robert Pugh and his son—I saw him reach up and take a quantity of coals from inside the barge, put them down into a cloth, tie it up, put it on his head, and come up the causeway—I stopped him when he came up—I asked where he got them—he said he picked them up out of the mud—I told him I had been watching him, and saw him take them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411213-name-330" type="witnessName">
